U.K. Tax-Evasion Convictions Rise After Crackdown, Guardian Says

-- B y   T o n y   C .   D r e i b u s
-- 
2011-08-27T08:59:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-27/u-k-tax-evasion-convictions-rise-after-crackdown-guardian-says.html
Tax-evasion  convictions are up 38
percent in the year through March after a crackdown by the U.K.
HM Revenue & Customs Service, The Guardian reported, citing law
firm McGrigors.  Some 148 people were convicted of tax evasion in the 12-
month period compared with 107 the prior year, according to The
Guardian.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony C. Dreibus in  London  at 
 tdreibus@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter@bloomberg.net . 